<item>
            <title>[PAY-4033] submerchant: consume WFC AchInformation + persist MaxRetryAttempts</title>
                <link>https://wellfit.atlassian.net/browse/PAY-4033</link>
                <project id="10016" key="PAY">Payments</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Stand up the first Service Bus consumer in submerchant-microservice to consume the existing &lt;tt&gt;WellfitConnect.AchInformation.Created&lt;/tt&gt; event (and &lt;tt&gt;.Updated&lt;/tt&gt; when WFC ships it) via an anti-corruption layer, upserting the &lt;tt&gt;AchLimitConfig&lt;/tt&gt; aggregate keyed on SubMerchantId.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Adds&lt;/b&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;a nullable &lt;tt&gt;MaxRetryAttempts&lt;/tt&gt; (tinyint, 0&#8211;2) column to &lt;tt&gt;Payments.AchLimitConfig&lt;/tt&gt; + aggregate property,&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;EF config,&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;DACPAC migration,&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;and per-env service-bus settings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Routing already in place:&lt;/b&gt; the event rides the existing &lt;tt&gt;accounts&lt;/tt&gt; EG Domain &#8594; &lt;tt&gt;accounts&lt;/tt&gt; SB topic forwarder (Terraform-owned, already live for other &lt;tt&gt;accounts&lt;/tt&gt;-topic consumers); the &lt;tt&gt;submerchant-api&lt;/tt&gt; subscription + its type filter is already staged in &lt;tt&gt;wellfit-payments/src/functions/payments-func/scripts/servicebus-topics/provision-sb-topics.sh:128&lt;/tt&gt; (commit &lt;tt&gt;41f2da655&lt;/tt&gt;, 2026-06-25). No new Terraform, no new EG subscription, no new SB topic &#8212; remaining infra work is running that script per env to materialize the subscription. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Closes the long-open Payments-side TODO from PLAT-3672/PLAT-3900; purely additive, REST PUT path untouched. Locked 2026-05-16 (D1&#8211;D12); routing corrected 2026-07-03 (D9/D10).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Open confirmations (non-blocking): publish-site (Q7) needs local/GHE re-confirm; product-scoping (D12, one product = one SubMerchantId) to confirm with an onboarding-flow expert.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Full analysis + solution: &lt;tt&gt;_bmad-output/products/payments/04_ExpresseLane/enhancement/wf-connect-ach-information-subscriber-ach-transaction-limits/&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
