                                                            <comment id="95751" author="712020:c31907b0-e8a3-4790-8686-3585fdb11873" created="Tue, 14 Jul 2026 12:22:04 -0700"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;How to use the E2E testing files attached to this story&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Attached: &lt;tt&gt;E2E_RUNBOOK.md&lt;/tt&gt;, the Postman collection (&lt;tt&gt;PAY-4033-wfc-ach-information.postman_collection.json&lt;/tt&gt;), and 2 Postman environment files (DEV, STAGE). Full detail + scenario matrix is in the runbook; quick start below.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Why runbook + Postman (not Playwright):&lt;/b&gt; the feature is a headless Service Bus consumer with no UI. You validate by injecting a &lt;tt&gt;WellfitConnect.AchInformation&lt;/tt&gt; event and inspecting the datastore/telemetry.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Quick start (DEV):&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In Postman, import the collection and the DEV environment; select the &quot;PAY-4033 DEV&quot; environment.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Fill the 2 secrets in the env (intentionally NOT committed):
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;tt&gt;sbSharedAccessKeyName&lt;/tt&gt; / &lt;tt&gt;sbSharedAccessKey&lt;/tt&gt; &#8212; a Send key on the &lt;tt&gt;accounts&lt;/tt&gt; SB topic (Portal: dev-sbns-payments-westus3 &#8594; Topics &#8594; accounts &#8594; Shared access policies). Paste ONLY the key value, not the whole connection string.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;tt&gt;egDomainKey&lt;/tt&gt; &#8212; the Event Grid domain key (Method B / request 2.1 only): &lt;tt&gt;az eventgrid domain key list --name dev-evgd-payments --resource-group dev-rg-plat-core-wus3 --query key1 -o tsv&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Set &lt;tt&gt;subMerchantId&lt;/tt&gt; to a REAL submerchant id (the DEV env is pre-set to a verified one). A synthetic/unknown id dead-letters with &quot;SubMerchant not found&quot; &#8212; the consumer requires the parent submerchant to exist. Verify a candidate with request 3.1 (200 = exists, 204 = does not).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Run the requests:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Folder 1 (Method A &#8212; recommended): direct Service Bus send. &lt;tt&gt;1.1&lt;/tt&gt; Created, &lt;tt&gt;1.2&lt;/tt&gt; Updated, &lt;tt&gt;1.3&lt;/tt&gt;&#8211;&lt;tt&gt;1.6&lt;/tt&gt; poison/negative. The SAS token is auto-minted by the collection&apos;s pre-request script.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Folder 2 (Method B): Event Grid domain publish (&lt;tt&gt;2.1&lt;/tt&gt;). Note: &lt;tt&gt;source&lt;/tt&gt; must be &lt;tt&gt;accounts&lt;/tt&gt; &#8212; on this domain the CloudEvent &lt;tt&gt;source&lt;/tt&gt; selects the domain topic.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Folder 3 (verify): &lt;tt&gt;3.1&lt;/tt&gt; GET submerchant (200 shows &lt;tt&gt;achLimits.perTransactionLimit&lt;/tt&gt; / &lt;tt&gt;dailyLimit&lt;/tt&gt;; 204 = unknown id), &lt;tt&gt;3.2&lt;/tt&gt; peek DLQ.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;How to read results:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Success (&lt;tt&gt;1.1&lt;/tt&gt; / &lt;tt&gt;2.1&lt;/tt&gt;): the subscription&apos;s dead-letter count does NOT increase, request &lt;tt&gt;3.1&lt;/tt&gt; shows the injected limits, and App Insights logs &quot;ACH limit config upserted from WFC AchInformation event&quot;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Poison (&lt;tt&gt;1.3&lt;/tt&gt;&#8211;&lt;tt&gt;1.6&lt;/tt&gt;): the dead-letter count rises by 1; no limits are written.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Easiest to watch counts live from the subscription page in the Azure Portal (dev-sbns-payments-westus3 &#8594; Topics &#8594; accounts &#8594; Subscriptions &#8594; submerchant-api).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Two standing items&lt;/b&gt; (in the runbook, not blockers for using the files): the &lt;tt&gt;accounts&lt;/tt&gt;/submerchant-api SB filter rule still needs to be authored in the Wellfit/Terraform repo (currently manual-only), and go-live is blocked by the WFC&#8594;Payments routing bridge.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Review PR: &lt;a href=&quot;https://wellfit-technologies-inc.ghe.com/Wellfit/bmad-wellfit/pull/3737&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noreferrer&quot;&gt;https://wellfit-technologies-inc.ghe.com/Wellfit/bmad-wellfit/pull/3737&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                                                            <comment id="95752" author="712020:c31907b0-e8a3-4790-8686-3585fdb11873" created="Tue, 14 Jul 2026 12:23:31 -0700"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://wellfit.atlassian.net/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?accountId=712020%3Aef9caae6-9c72-4f4b-ad51-72da2faad9c6&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;712020:ef9caae6-9c72-4f4b-ad51-72da2faad9c6&quot; data-account-id=&quot;712020:ef9caae6-9c72-4f4b-ad51-72da2faad9c6&quot; accountid=&quot;712020:ef9caae6-9c72-4f4b-ad51-72da2faad9c6&quot; rel=&quot;noreferrer&quot;&gt;Christopher Ariel Valenzuela Medina&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://wellfit.atlassian.net/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?accountId=712020%3A00fbd106-0c2e-4908-85c4-2c029b26d57e&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;712020:00fbd106-0c2e-4908-85c4-2c029b26d57e&quot; data-account-id=&quot;712020:00fbd106-0c2e-4908-85c4-2c029b26d57e&quot; accountid=&quot;712020:00fbd106-0c2e-4908-85c4-2c029b26d57e&quot; rel=&quot;noreferrer&quot;&gt;Shikha Atal&lt;/a&gt; &lt;br/&gt;
